descript.abstract: GIS representation of the UDOT Route System (main routes, ramps and collectors). Routes are represented as PolylineM features where the m coordinate is in miles. PolylineMs have been calibrated at end points and also some intermediate points as described in the UDOT linear referencing system (LRS) route descriptions for state route junctions, interstate bridge deck (begin and end) and other miscellaneous features.Last Updated: February 6, 2013
descript.purpose: Visual representation of the UDOT LRS system which is mostly tablular data collected with field inventory vehicles.

dataIdInfo.idAbs:
GIS representation of the UDOT Route System (main routes, ramps and collectors). Routes are represented as PolylineM features where the m coordinate is in miles. PolylineMs have been calibrated at end points and also some intermediate points as described in the UDOT linear referencing system (LRS) route descriptions for state route junctions, interstate bridge deck (begin and end) and other miscellaneous features.

Updated: June 3, 2015

cntaddr.addrtype: REQUIRED: The mailing and/or physical address for the organization or individual.
cntaddr.city: REQUIRED: The city of the address.
cntaddr.state: REQUIRED: The state or province of the address.
cntaddr.postal: REQUIRED: The ZIP or other postal code of the address.

cntinfo.cntvoice: REQUIRED: The telephone number by which individuals can speak to the organization or individual.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: UDOT Route Name (Unique Name for Route)
Direction of Route (P = North or East bound; N (for divided only) is Southbound or Westbound
Route Type (M = Main, R = Ramp, C = Collector, X = Other)
Ramp subnumber for a given interchange system
Short description of route (including ramps, collectors, etc)
Date feature deprecated, not used currently
Notes on why feature is deprecated (realignment, etc)
Notes on circumstances leading to the feature being added to the LRS geometry.
Composite of RouteName, RouteDir (and includes type, interchange, and rampnumber for Ramp, Collector, and 'Other' type route features.
Miscellaneous designation useful for cartographic subqueries
